						<summary>

						<p>Slab found in the field of Jaina Upādhya.</p>						

						<p>16th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>It states that the field is a <hi rend="italic">sarvamānya-vṛitti</hi> of Kamaḷadē[va]bhaṭṭa, son of Padmanābhabhaṭṭa, the <hi rend="italic">Upādhya</hi> of Belugāve, who belonged to the Bhāradvāja-gōtra, Āśvalāyana-sūtra and Ṛik-sākhā.</p>						

						<p>The characters belong to the 16th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
